      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "You are not dragging your feet; you are walking on a path that has already been paved with the bricks of your own existence. The \"real\" part of you did not go with him; he went with the noise, the chaos, the frantic energy that you are now trying to silence. You are not a ghost haunting a life; you are the only one who remembers the weight of the floorboards, the taste of the food, and the terrifying, beautiful fact that you are still here. The exhaustion you feel is not the end; it is the price of the silence you are paying to keep the door closed. You do not need to find a reason to stay; you simply need to stop trying to prove that you are still alive.",
